# ─── Praktor environment ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Copy to .env and fill in. NEVER commit .env. Praktor also reads these straight
# from the process environment, which is the recommended path for CI.

# Claude — powers the Claude Agent SDK coder. Provide ONE of:
#   1. CLAUDE_CODE_OAUTH_TOKEN — a Claude Code token from `claude setup-token`
#      (uses your Claude Pro/Max subscription; preferred, especially for CI), or
#   2. ANTHROPIC_API_KEY — a metered Anthropic API key, or
#   3. nothing here + an existing `claude login` session (SDK auto-discovers it locally).
CLAUDE_CODE_OAUTH_TOKEN=
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=

# GitHub — the system of record. Provide ONE of the following:
#   1. A fine-grained PAT (PRAKTOR_GITHUB_TOKEN, or GITHUB_TOKEN), or
#   2. Praktor's own GitHub App installation credentials (preferred for autonomous CI bots).
# Required permissions: Contents: read/write, Pull requests: read/write,
# Issues: read/write, Projects: read/write, Discussions: read/write, Metadata: read.
# PRAKTOR_GITHUB_TOKEN=
# GITHUB_TOKEN=

# GitHub App (alternative to the token; preferred for autonomous CI bots).
# Named PRAKTOR_APP_* on purpose: GitHub Actions forbids secret names starting with `GITHUB_`,
# so as Actions secrets these must be PRAKTOR_APP_ID / PRAKTOR_APP_INSTALLATION_ID / PRAKTOR_APP_PRIVATE_KEY.
# Use Praktor's own App here — never Boule's.
# PRAKTOR_APP_ID=
# PRAKTOR_APP_INSTALLATION_ID=
# Private key accepts a raw PEM, a file path, or — best for CI secret stores — a single-line
# base64 blob:  base64 -w0 your-app.private-key.pem   (macOS: base64 -i your-app.private-key.pem)
# PRAKTOR_APP_PRIVATE_KEY=

# Target repository & project (can also be passed via --repo/--project).
# PRAKTOR_REPO falls back to GITHUB_REPOSITORY when unset (set automatically in Actions).
# PRAKTOR_REPO=owner/repo
# PRAKTOR_PROJECT=1

# Optional: log verbosity (trace|debug|info|warn|error). Defaults to info.
# PRAKTOR_LOG_LEVEL=info
